I couldn't wait any longer, goddammit.

66
00:06:16,834 --> 00:06:17,710
You want this?

67
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:20,338
Seriously?

68
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:24,675
Why the hell is everyone
always asking me to find people?

69
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,803
What am I, the North Star? Damn it.

70
00:06:30,431 --> 00:06:31,265
Where’d she go?

71
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:32,558
What now?

72
00:06:35,686 --> 00:06:36,646
Jo Jae-mi.

73
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:38,815
-Well--
-Spill it.

74
00:06:40,274 --> 00:06:42,693
Hae Jo's dying
and she's dragging him around.

75
00:06:43,277 --> 00:06:46,823
Wait, what's all this that I'm hearing?

76
00:06:47,824 --> 00:06:48,825
Hey, you're here!

77
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:50,701
That little…

78
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:52,495
-Damn.
-And who are you?

79
00:06:53,579 --> 00:06:56,541
And why are you looking for Jae-mi?

80
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:59,168
To find my boy.

81
00:07:00,002 --> 00:07:01,337
Oh God.

82
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:04,966
That means we're in this together.

83
00:07:13,057 --> 00:07:15,309
-Hey, you're bleeding.
-I'm all right.

84
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:16,644
What?

85
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:27,738
HAE JO
THIS TIME, I'LL FIND YOU!

86
00:07:30,575 --> 00:07:35,621
SO JUST STAY ALIVE!!!

87
00:07:39,917 --> 00:07:42,086
Please.

88
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:53,473
Come here instead
of the Internet café. Quick!

89
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:55,892
22, TOEJEONG ROAD, ALLEY 47

90
00:07:58,519 --> 00:07:59,520
Excuse me, sir.

91
00:08:03,566 --> 00:08:05,109
Where are we going after this?

92
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:06,652
I don't know.

93
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:10,239
There's no place I want to be.

94
00:08:14,452 --> 00:08:15,912
What about your father?

95
00:08:17,747 --> 00:08:20,416
What's the point?
Jae-mi's not with me anymore.

96
00:08:30,426 --> 00:08:33,554
You really should eat,
even if you don't have an appetite.

97
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:36,098
Your meds are strong.

98
00:08:40,144 --> 00:08:41,979
Appetite is a funny thing.

99
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,857
I was so hungry I could've eaten a horse.

100
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:47,860
But since throwing up, I can't face food.

101
00:08:49,487 --> 00:08:50,863
Still, you need to eat.

102
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:55,826
My mother always says
that if you still can take a bite,

103
00:08:57,245 --> 00:08:59,247
you have at least ten more years in you.

104
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:03,709
So take five bites
and you'll make it to 80.

105
00:09:14,303 --> 00:09:16,305
Come on, just five bites.

106
00:09:18,266 --> 00:09:19,308
Open wide.

107
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:22,853
Come on, be a good boy.

108
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:27,483
Knock, knock. Open up, please.

109
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:30,778
I'll spank you if you don't.

110
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:37,743
Fine, then don't.

111
00:09:39,203 --> 00:09:40,663
Don't eat.

112
00:09:41,622 --> 00:09:44,584
You never listened to your mother
while growing up, did you?

113
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:48,004
How did you know?

114
00:09:50,172 --> 00:09:52,925
I'm still being punished for that.

115
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:01,183
What is with you today?

116
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:04,812
I'm tired of playing LEGO with Dad.

117
00:10:04,895 --> 00:10:07,148
Please give me
a little brother or a sister.

118
00:10:07,231 --> 00:10:10,067
-Tired of LEGO? Then paint with me.
-Seung-hyeok!

119
00:10:11,319 --> 00:10:12,278
Son!

120
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:21,829
-Is Seung-hyeok here?
-What? I don't know.

121
00:10:21,912 --> 00:10:23,539
He wanted to play LEGO.

122
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:25,625
Hey, Seung-hyeok!

123
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:32,131
Mom! I want a brother or a sister!

124
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:34,842
Stop painting and make me one.

125
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:39,180
Doctor, I was just wondering
if it would be possible

126
00:10:39,263 --> 00:10:42,266
to use my husband’s frozen sperm again

127
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:44,769
for another baby?

128
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:49,315
Really?

129
00:10:49,982 --> 00:10:51,317
Yes, thank you.

130
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:54,779
I was the reason everyone became unhappy.

131
00:10:56,572 --> 00:10:58,407
Pandora's box was now open.

132
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:04,372
And my mom found out
that I came from some stranger's sperm.

133
00:11:05,456 --> 00:11:08,084
-Nice.
-Nice. One.

134
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:11,003
-You see how the ball bounces out?
-Yes.

135
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:14,590
When it hits the glove,
close your hand so it doesn't bounce out.

136
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:16,217
-Okay.
-You got this?

137
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,176
Yes, I got it.

138
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:22,264
-It went over the fence! Over the fence!
-Wow! It's a home run! Yes!

139
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:27,269
-Home run!
-Home run, yay!

140
00:11:29,814 --> 00:11:32,400
-Dad! I got a perfect score!
-That's my boy.

141
00:11:32,483 --> 00:11:36,070
Great job! You got a perfect score!

142
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:39,573
Mom was going to keep it a secret forever.

143
00:11:40,282 --> 00:11:41,701
What? A brother or sister?

144
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:45,913
Quiet. Mom told me not to tell you.

145
00:11:45,996 --> 00:11:48,499
Okay, I'll keep it a secret. I promise.

146
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:51,127
But I blew it.

147
00:11:53,713 --> 00:11:55,423
I'm so sorry.

148
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:57,299
I don't know what to tell you.

149
00:11:58,092 --> 00:11:58,926
Sir,

150
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:01,679
we'll take legal responsibility.

151
00:12:01,762 --> 00:12:03,597
When were you going to tell me?

152
00:12:05,641 --> 00:12:06,600
Never.

153
00:12:06,684 --> 00:12:07,601
Never?

154
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:12,565
Don't you know
what having a child means to me?

155
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:14,900
I was willing to die, Hae-won!

156
00:12:14,984 --> 00:12:18,237
I risked my life to have our child!

157
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:24,243
But you were going
to make a fool of me forever?

158
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:26,120
How could you?

159
00:12:26,203 --> 00:12:27,163
What now, then?

160
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:30,791
Want to get rid of him?

161
00:12:33,586 --> 00:12:34,420
What?

162
00:12:34,503 --> 00:12:38,632
You're too worried about your reputation
to do that anyway.

163
00:12:40,134 --> 00:12:42,470
It would've been better
if you didn't know.

164
00:12:42,970 --> 00:12:46,182
Then you could've carried on
being a good dad!

165
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,266
What's the point?

166
00:12:49,935 --> 00:12:51,771
He's not even mine!

167
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:53,749
Honey.

168
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:56,627
Are you asleep?

169
00:14:00,464 --> 00:14:01,549
Mom.

170
00:14:04,718 --> 00:14:05,928
Are you going somewhere?

171
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:12,184
Do you want to go stargazing with me?

172
00:14:14,478 --> 00:14:16,730
No, I'm sleepy.

173
00:14:31,036 --> 00:14:32,037
All right.

174
00:14:34,623 --> 00:14:35,457
Go to sleep.

175
00:14:53,183 --> 00:14:56,020
Honestly, I was scared.

176
00:14:57,938 --> 00:15:01,942
Scared I might never see Dad again
if I went with her.

177
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:07,781
Are you Seong Hae-won's husband?

178
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:12,286
We found your wife's car this morning
at the bottom of Mount Baegun.

179
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:13,203
But that choice

180
00:15:14,955 --> 00:15:17,207
led to the complete opposite result.

181
00:15:54,745 --> 00:15:55,996
Dad.

182
00:15:56,580 --> 00:15:58,666
I don't need a brother or sister anymore.

183
00:16:02,086 --> 00:16:04,421
All I need is you.

184
00:16:24,483 --> 00:16:26,235
What scared and upset me

185
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:29,530
more than my mom's death

186
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:32,616
was the thought of being abandoned.

187
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:35,744
I was only eight.

188
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:38,872
Eight years old.

189
00:16:41,959 --> 00:16:44,545
Dad, would you like to play LEGO with me?

190
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:46,171
I earned a new belt…

191
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:55,347
I came from a stranger's seed,

192
00:16:55,431 --> 00:16:58,600
but if I stood my ground,
maybe I'd be able to put down roots.

193
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:03,063
I could be so naive.

194
00:17:15,617 --> 00:17:17,244
Let's have Jjajangmyeon.

195
00:17:18,495 --> 00:17:20,622
I'll wait for you outside school at noon.

196
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:38,724
CONGRATULATIONS CLASS OF 2011

197
00:17:38,807 --> 00:17:40,642
It was my graduation day.

198
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:44,688
It was the perfect time to choose my path.

199
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:52,613
If he came, I was going to go back home.

200
00:17:53,822 --> 00:17:57,117
If he didn't come,
I was going to wander around forever

201
00:17:57,785 --> 00:17:59,203
without putting down roots.

202
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:08,170
So I hoped he would come.

203
00:18:10,047 --> 00:18:11,590
"Please show up for me."

204
00:18:16,011 --> 00:18:17,721
That day, I threw it all away.

205
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:22,643
The man who was once my dad,
my life as Chae Seung-hyeok…

206
00:18:23,143 --> 00:18:24,019
EXCELLENCE AWARD

207
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:26,396
…and my belief in unconditional love.

208
00:18:27,022 --> 00:18:28,023
Everything.

209
00:18:38,659 --> 00:18:40,828
It was the worst cold spell in a century.

210
00:18:43,789 --> 00:18:47,835
But since I came from frozen sperm,
I've always been built for the cold.

211
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:49,294
My God.

212
00:18:52,047 --> 00:18:54,299
The toughest thing was hunger, you know.

213
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:56,552
A teenage boy could die

214
00:18:57,845 --> 00:18:59,304
after ten days without food.

215
00:19:00,639 --> 00:19:02,349
How did you manage to get by?

216
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:04,852
I didn't.

217
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:09,398
I’d resorted to digging through trash
but then I hit the jackpot of my life.

218
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:10,983
Jackpot?

219
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:16,989
Hey, are you homeless?

220
00:19:17,072 --> 00:19:17,948
DRUMSTICK CHICKEN

221
00:19:18,031 --> 00:19:18,907
That day,

222
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:23,412
I used up the last bit of luck I had left.

223
00:19:28,917 --> 00:19:30,836
-Let's go.
-Where?

224
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:32,629
To hit up my jackpot.

225
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:09,374
Wait, how are you two together?

226
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,964
Kkari. Where's Hae Jo?

227
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:18,842
-Hey, how did you get here?
-What?

228
00:20:18,926 --> 00:20:21,345
That's what I want to ask you. Come here.

229
00:20:21,428 --> 00:20:22,304
Hey, I--

230
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,182
We need to talk.

231
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:28,227
But…

232
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:31,230
What the hell is going on?

233
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:35,150
I told you she wasn't with him.
Give me back my phone.

234
00:20:36,735 --> 00:20:38,695
Why do you need my phone?

235
00:20:44,993 --> 00:20:45,869
EO HEUNG

236
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:51,750
The number you have dialed is currently…

237
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:54,086
What's going on?

238
00:20:54,169 --> 00:20:56,463
Send him a message to give you a call.

239
00:20:56,964 --> 00:20:57,881
Say it's urgent.

240
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:01,802
No, actually,
tell him to come meet you here.

241
00:21:01,885 --> 00:21:03,262
He'll listen to you.

242
00:21:03,345 --> 00:21:05,013
Did something happen to him?

243
00:21:06,473 --> 00:21:08,642
He didn't run away from home, did he?

244
00:21:13,272 --> 00:21:14,231
No way.

245
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:16,858
He really is a man of his word.

246
00:21:19,861 --> 00:21:20,737
You know,

247
00:21:22,614 --> 00:21:23,865
I ran away from home.

248
00:21:24,449 --> 00:21:25,534
What?

249
00:21:30,956 --> 00:21:33,583
Well, look at you.

250
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:36,044
You're a BR then. You're a BR.

251
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:38,588
-What's that?
-A BR. You don't know?

252
00:21:38,672 --> 00:21:41,174
Like BI, beginner investor.
Or BG, beginner golfer.

253
00:21:41,258 --> 00:21:42,884
BR is a beginner runaway.

254
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:46,680
I've been a runaway for 14 years.
So technically, I'm your senior.

255
00:21:46,763 --> 00:21:48,849
-Excuse me, Mr. Senior.
-Yes.

256
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:53,520
You might think it's shameless
and ungrateful of me to say this,

257
00:21:53,603 --> 00:21:54,438
but honestly…

258
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:58,233
I'm a little jealous of you.

259
00:22:00,610 --> 00:22:02,946
-What do you mean?
-The way you live your life.

260
00:22:03,447 --> 00:22:06,700
It looks like you do as you please
without giving it much thought,

261
00:22:06,783 --> 00:22:08,118
but to me,

262
00:22:10,412 --> 00:22:11,371
it's impressive.

263
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:17,586
It’s pretty cool, actually.

264
00:22:18,962 --> 00:22:21,923
I’ve always followed orders

265
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:24,926
and never stepped out of line.

266
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:31,933
I was cold, I was hungry,

267
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:34,436
and I didn't know where to go

268
00:22:36,063 --> 00:22:39,191
or what I should do
to be happy like other people.

269
00:22:41,401 --> 00:22:44,154
It was my decision to leave home.

270
00:22:47,324 --> 00:22:50,243
But I wished somebody would come
and take me in

271
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:54,748
like an abandoned dog.

272
00:22:59,002 --> 00:23:00,295
Then you called me.

273
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:01,254
ASSHOLE

274
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:05,342
You said you were going to dump Jae-mi,

275
00:23:06,593 --> 00:23:08,095
and I could come if I wanted.

276
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:11,932
Not to take her back though.

277
00:23:14,059 --> 00:23:14,935
Forget it.

278
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:17,145
I'm never gonna let you have her.

279
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:18,855
-Why not?
-I'd be too jealous.

280
00:23:18,939 --> 00:23:20,524
I'd hate to die a jealous man.

281
00:23:20,607 --> 00:23:23,693
Learn to be happy on your own.
Not together with her.

282
00:23:23,777 --> 00:23:26,446
Wow, you really are an asshole.

283
00:23:28,281 --> 00:23:31,243
Still, as a veteran runaway,
let me give you some tips.

284
00:23:33,286 --> 00:23:35,205
Never set a destination.

285
00:23:35,288 --> 00:23:38,291
You feel like you must do something?
Well, fuck that shit.

286
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:40,836
Just let your instincts guide you.

287
00:23:40,919 --> 00:23:42,587
That way, you won't get lost.

288
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:46,842
You throw yourself into the unknown,
then you're not adrift anymore.

289
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:48,635
You become a drifter.

290
00:23:50,137 --> 00:23:51,471
What bullshit.

291
00:23:52,139 --> 00:23:54,349
-Moo.
-Moo.

292
00:23:59,896 --> 00:24:01,690
Why did you want to do this?

293
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:03,525
Why not? It's liberating.

294
00:24:03,608 --> 00:24:06,778
-I don't have a towel.
-Hey, what are you doing?

295
00:24:06,862 --> 00:24:08,113
Hey, stop!

296
00:24:08,196 --> 00:24:10,240
-But you'll hit me!
-No, come back.

297
00:24:10,323 --> 00:24:12,200
Grow up already.

298
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:15,871
Hey, Heung! Seriously?

299
00:24:18,081 --> 00:24:19,332
Knock, knock, drink up.

300
00:24:19,416 --> 00:24:21,585
Fine, but don't say "Knock, knock."

301
00:24:26,214 --> 00:24:28,216
You've got to knock first.

302
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,177
Are you insane? Just eat.

303
00:24:30,677 --> 00:24:32,762
Knock, knock!

304
00:24:33,346 --> 00:24:34,598
You'll get us killed!

305
00:24:34,681 --> 00:24:37,142
It'd be nice to die together. Let's do it.

306
00:24:37,767 --> 00:24:39,936
-You want to die, do you?
-Hey, okay.

307
00:24:41,771 --> 00:24:42,731
For God's sake.

308
00:24:43,398 --> 00:24:44,816
How long does this take?

309
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:47,068
Here.

310
00:24:57,746 --> 00:25:00,790
THE PATH TO THE WORLD
WELCOME TO SEOUL

311
00:25:02,292 --> 00:25:05,629
I left him a voicemail
saying to call me as soon as he gets it.

312
00:25:06,713 --> 00:25:09,216
Now it's down to him.

313
00:25:10,258 --> 00:25:12,719
Well, would you like some tea?

314
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:14,513
You're a saint.

315
00:25:15,722 --> 00:25:18,183
Being so nice to me
after all I've done to you.

316
00:25:21,478 --> 00:25:22,854
I'm doing it for myself.

317
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:27,400
I feel like if I'm rude,
you'll show up in my dreams

318
00:25:27,484 --> 00:25:30,028
saying "I want my son back,"
strangling me--

319
00:25:30,111 --> 00:25:31,238
What?

320
00:25:33,365 --> 00:25:35,575
You can be suffocating sometimes,

321
00:25:36,451 --> 00:25:38,828
but you're a great mom really.

322
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:43,708
What kind of sugarcoated insult was that?

323
00:25:44,417 --> 00:25:47,337
You never gave up on your child.

324
00:25:47,420 --> 00:25:50,340
You nourished him and raised him well.

325
00:25:52,717 --> 00:25:56,888
Boy, I should've had a daughter like you.

326
00:25:57,973 --> 00:26:01,643
I insisted on having a son
to carry on the stupid family line,

327
00:26:01,726 --> 00:26:02,686
and now here I am.

328
00:26:02,769 --> 00:26:04,688
Goddamn it.

329
00:26:06,147 --> 00:26:07,899
Sorry to interrupt.

330
00:26:07,983 --> 00:26:10,694
I have a question.
How did you two end up in Hongcheon?

331
00:26:11,695 --> 00:26:13,697
Gwangmyeong is the address I gave.

332
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:15,949
And how do you know that kidnapper?

333
00:26:16,491 --> 00:26:18,785
-Why Hongcheon?
-For some beef?

334
00:26:18,868 --> 00:26:21,621
-Are you together?
-Did you have a fight? Why--

335
00:26:21,705 --> 00:26:22,872
My mom!

336
00:26:27,794 --> 00:26:30,088
Hae Jo left me

337
00:26:30,755 --> 00:26:32,757
at my mother's house.

338
00:26:33,425 --> 00:26:36,595
I had never met her in my life.

339
00:26:45,061 --> 00:26:47,689
I guess he wanted to find out
my actual birthday.

340
00:26:47,772 --> 00:26:52,652
I hated that my official date of birth
was the day I was left at the orphanage,

341
00:26:52,736 --> 00:26:58,033
so I always picked some random day
and said that was my birthday.

342
00:27:00,493 --> 00:27:03,580
So? When is your real birthday?

343
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:09,377
It's the same. The day I was left.

344
00:27:09,461 --> 00:27:13,465
Goddamn animal! She abandoned her child
as soon as she gave birth to her?

345
00:27:14,132 --> 00:27:15,550
That's no mother.

346
00:27:15,634 --> 00:27:18,553
She deserves to be beaten to a pulp.

347
00:27:18,637 --> 00:27:19,721
Hey, John!

348
00:27:20,472 --> 00:27:23,058
-Damn.
-No need.

349
00:27:23,558 --> 00:27:25,393
I have guys out there. Her address?

350
00:27:25,477 --> 00:27:26,311
Hang on.

351
00:27:26,394 --> 00:27:28,313
No one uses physical force these days.

352
00:27:28,396 --> 00:27:30,690
I can expose her online.

353
00:27:30,774 --> 00:27:32,233
Name and date of birth?

354
00:27:33,401 --> 00:27:37,155
I didn't know you all had my back.
That makes me so happy!

355
00:27:37,238 --> 00:27:38,198
Her address!

356
00:27:38,281 --> 00:27:41,451
I'm being serious.
Don't protect her because she's your mom.

357
00:27:41,534 --> 00:27:43,828
Name and date of birth. I'm so pissed.

358
00:27:43,912 --> 00:27:47,916
Wow. You know what? Drinks are on me.

359
00:27:47,999 --> 00:27:50,293
Ju-ri. Can we raid your bar?

360
00:27:50,377 --> 00:27:51,628
But you lost your wallet.

361
00:27:53,588 --> 00:27:55,465
And I never sell on credit.

362
00:27:57,759 --> 00:27:59,386
Hey, Mother's treat.

363
00:28:01,054 --> 00:28:02,514
-Oh, really?
-Yes.

364
00:28:02,597 --> 00:28:03,556
Really?

365
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:06,267
-That's cool of you.
-No one's ever done this for me!

366
00:28:07,477 --> 00:28:08,603
I'm freaking jealous.

367
00:28:09,312 --> 00:28:10,855
Fried chicken delivery!

368
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:28,123
-Shit.
-Damn.

369
00:28:28,206 --> 00:28:30,500
-Stop!
-Run!

370
00:28:30,583 --> 00:28:31,960
You jerk!

371
00:28:32,544 --> 00:28:35,547
-Heung, it's me!
-Hey, that hurts!

372
00:28:35,630 --> 00:28:37,966
-That hurts!
-You think this hurts?

373
00:28:47,726 --> 00:28:49,936
What's with the long face? You hit me.

374
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:51,563
That's not fair.

375
00:28:52,689 --> 00:28:54,649
You're not sorry at all, are you?

376
00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:58,111
What, should I shake my butt again?

377
00:28:58,987 --> 00:29:01,281
You're unbelievable. Unbelievable.

378
00:29:01,781 --> 00:29:04,909
You were unconscious, then you vanished.
Is that funny to you?

379
00:29:06,911 --> 00:29:08,121
Why didn't you call?

380
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:11,458
You could've at least texted me,
for God's sake.

381
00:29:11,541 --> 00:29:14,210
I was worried sick.
Did it never occur to you?

382
00:29:14,294 --> 00:29:16,546
No, I guess it didn't.

383
00:29:18,381 --> 00:29:21,634
Come on, why would I think about you?
You're nobody to me.

384
00:29:22,385 --> 00:29:24,304
You're not my girlfriend or my mom.

385
00:29:24,804 --> 00:29:27,974
You just took in some poor fucking kid
for a while. That's all.

386
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:33,271
Just think of me
as a stray dog you took in

387
00:29:33,354 --> 00:29:36,816
because you were lonely
and needed some warmth, okay?

388
00:29:39,736 --> 00:29:40,570
Are you scared?

389
00:29:45,825 --> 00:29:47,327
Don't act all tough.

390
00:29:48,453 --> 00:29:49,287
Everyone

391
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:52,832
is scared of death.

392
00:29:59,088 --> 00:30:00,089
Hae Jo.

393
00:30:01,591 --> 00:30:04,969
You're not going to die.
So don't be scared, okay?

394
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:15,313
-Bong-suk.
-Yes?

395
00:30:17,398 --> 00:30:18,483
I…

396
00:30:20,527 --> 00:30:21,611
can't sleep.

397
00:30:23,780 --> 00:30:27,951
I really want to sleep,
but my head hurts too much.

398
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:31,955
It feels like
my brain’s full of tangled threads.

399
00:30:32,038 --> 00:30:33,581
I'm losing my fucking memory.

400
00:30:35,458 --> 00:30:37,502
What if I completely lose my mind soon?

401
00:30:38,086 --> 00:30:40,088
What if I die alone somewhere?

402
00:30:41,297 --> 00:30:42,674
No, you won't.

403
00:30:43,424 --> 00:30:45,093
I'll never let that happen.

404
00:30:55,728 --> 00:30:57,021
What did I ever do?

405
00:30:59,774 --> 00:31:00,608
Huh?

406
00:31:03,611 --> 00:31:05,113
What did I do to deserve this?

407
00:31:06,698 --> 00:31:08,700
Being born by accident,

408
00:31:10,368 --> 00:31:11,744
left to wander the streets,

409
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:16,207
and suddenly die
as if struck by lightning?

410
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:26,342
I was abandoned.

411
00:31:27,844 --> 00:31:29,596
No one came looking for me.

412
00:31:34,893 --> 00:31:35,727
Why?

413
00:31:39,105 --> 00:31:42,108
So why do I have to be discarded?

414
00:31:44,652 --> 00:31:45,486
Huh?

415
00:32:00,376 --> 00:32:01,336
Why do I…

416
00:32:05,298 --> 00:32:06,299
Why do I…

417
00:32:07,675 --> 00:32:08,801
Why do I have to…

418
00:32:12,722 --> 00:32:14,307
Why me?

419
00:33:03,898 --> 00:33:05,108
Your phone.

420
00:33:06,442 --> 00:33:07,902
Oh, right.

421
00:33:21,958 --> 00:33:25,586
MOTHER - WHERE THE HELL ARE YOU?
DO YOU WANT ME TO DROP DEAD?

422
00:33:33,886 --> 00:33:34,721
Open it.

423
00:33:36,139 --> 00:33:36,973
Okay.

424
00:33:41,102 --> 00:33:42,061
The door.

425
00:33:43,146 --> 00:33:44,313
Open it and get out.

426
00:33:44,897 --> 00:33:45,815
Me?

427
00:33:47,608 --> 00:33:48,526
Okay.

428
00:33:56,075 --> 00:33:58,578
Mother?

429
00:33:59,787 --> 00:34:00,663
What…

430
00:34:03,166 --> 00:34:04,208
Mother.

431
00:34:15,970 --> 00:34:16,888
Hello?

432
00:34:18,222 --> 00:34:19,432
Go and have your fun.

433
00:34:21,100 --> 00:34:22,769
Have all the fun you want,

434
00:34:23,519 --> 00:34:24,604
then come home

435
00:34:25,980 --> 00:34:29,233
when you’ve had enough
and miss my cooking.

436
00:34:33,821 --> 00:34:36,908
But please keep your phone on.

437
00:34:36,991 --> 00:34:40,870
And try to stick to the main roads, okay?

438
00:34:40,953 --> 00:34:44,373
When you cross the street,
use the pedestrian overpass.

439
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:47,085
Mom.

440
00:34:49,712 --> 00:34:50,671
Yes?

441
00:34:52,423 --> 00:34:53,633
How's your back doing?

442
00:34:54,133 --> 00:34:57,845
You threw your back out the other day.
Are you feeling better now?

443
00:34:57,929 --> 00:35:01,474
Oh, for God's sake.
I'll be fine once I lose a little weight.

444
00:35:01,557 --> 00:35:05,186
You need to lose a lot. Maybe ten kilos.

445
00:35:05,269 --> 00:35:07,730
I'm hanging up! You're making me carsick.

446
00:35:24,622 --> 00:35:27,667
John, mind if I borrow those things again?

447
00:35:37,176 --> 00:35:38,177
Listen.

448
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:41,389
Don't go back to America.

449
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:44,058
Why don't you just stay here?

450
00:35:47,353 --> 00:35:48,980
You can be my second son.

451
00:35:54,443 --> 00:35:55,444
Forget it, then.

452
00:35:59,699 --> 00:36:01,534
Fine, I'll stay then.

453
00:36:03,202 --> 00:36:04,036
Mom.

454
00:36:58,174 --> 00:37:01,677
Wow. I didn't think
I'd be giving you this again.

455
00:37:05,097 --> 00:37:07,099
Here. Wipe your face with it.

456
00:37:13,564 --> 00:37:15,900
Somebody blew their nose in it earlier,

457
00:37:15,983 --> 00:37:17,818
so I was going to toss it.

458
00:37:18,319 --> 00:37:19,237
But

459
00:37:20,655 --> 00:37:23,866
if you want, you can wash it and keep it.

460
00:37:34,502 --> 00:37:36,587
You always give, and I always take.

461
00:37:38,047 --> 00:37:39,423
Like with these shoes.

462
00:37:40,508 --> 00:37:42,301
You've given me much more.

463
00:37:44,553 --> 00:37:47,223
You said I was a tiger now,
not a whimpering dog.

464
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:50,601
You made that possible, Jae-mi.

465
00:37:53,813 --> 00:37:54,855
Thank you.

466
00:37:59,819 --> 00:38:03,906
But honestly, don't you think
the shoes I got you were prettier?

467
00:38:06,450 --> 00:38:07,827
They were.

468
00:38:08,452 --> 00:38:10,037
Where are they?

469
00:38:10,663 --> 00:38:11,914
I threw them away.

470
00:38:12,915 --> 00:38:15,251
Over the roof of a restaurant in Namwon.

471
00:38:16,460 --> 00:38:18,504
-Hey, come here.
-What?

472
00:38:24,093 --> 00:38:26,304
Beat him to a pulp, Jae-mi!

473
00:38:38,566 --> 00:38:40,776
Hey, where are we going?

474
00:38:42,737 --> 00:38:45,281
You gonna bury me
in the woods or something?

475
00:38:47,408 --> 00:38:50,453
Fine, go ahead.
Bong-suk did the left, you do the right.

476
00:38:50,536 --> 00:38:51,579
Come on, slap me.

477
00:38:53,914 --> 00:38:54,999
Just do it. Go on.

478
00:38:57,251 --> 00:39:00,087
Why would I hit you? I want to hug you.

479
00:39:02,298 --> 00:39:03,132
Such a good boy.

480
00:39:03,841 --> 00:39:07,511
Hey, I can't breathe.
Wait. I can't breathe, okay?

481
00:39:07,595 --> 00:39:08,596
Thank you.

482
00:39:09,930 --> 00:39:11,932
For finding out my real birthday.

483
00:39:13,142 --> 00:39:14,935
And for coming back safely.

484
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:17,897
Thank you so much.

485
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:56,602
Ow! Hey!

486
00:39:57,395 --> 00:39:58,979
That knock some sense into you?

487
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:02,483
What the fuck? This is a nuclear bomb.
What if it explodes?

488
00:40:02,566 --> 00:40:04,402
-Well, it didn't.
-Hey.

489
00:40:04,485 --> 00:40:07,363
I am grateful,
but you totally deserved that.

490
00:40:07,446 --> 00:40:10,032
I found out my birthday
but why run off like that?

491
00:40:10,116 --> 00:40:11,367
Hey, remember this?

492
00:40:11,450 --> 00:40:15,830
You told me to stay
and said you'd protect me from lightning.

493
00:40:15,913 --> 00:40:18,541
You promised to take care of me forever,

494
00:40:18,624 --> 00:40:20,501
then you ditched me and ran away?

495
00:40:20,584 --> 00:40:23,045
It's the best thing
I could've done before I die.

496
00:40:23,129 --> 00:40:24,255
Are you serious?

497
00:40:24,338 --> 00:40:26,507
Yet your last dying word to me was "shit."

498
00:40:26,590 --> 00:40:28,509
What are you talking about?

499
00:40:28,592 --> 00:40:32,221
When you were on the brink of death
after getting stabbed on that island.

500
00:40:35,975 --> 00:40:37,560
Sh…

501
00:40:38,310 --> 00:40:39,186
Sh…

502
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:40,312
"Shit"?

503
00:40:42,523 --> 00:40:43,357
Oh my God.

504
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:47,528
What? You're pretending
like you don't remember again.

505
00:40:47,611 --> 00:40:50,656
Oh my God! You idiot!

506
00:40:53,075 --> 00:40:54,452
I wasn't saying "shit."

507
00:40:54,994 --> 00:40:59,832
I was saying "shoes."
These shoes you bought me! God.

508
00:41:01,417 --> 00:41:03,669
Shoes? What about the shoes? Why?

509
00:41:03,752 --> 00:41:08,007
When we were on that island
and you asked me to come with you,

510
00:41:08,674 --> 00:41:10,885
I actually wanted to go

511
00:41:12,136 --> 00:41:14,388
wearing the shoes you got me.

512
00:41:17,933 --> 00:41:21,312
That's what I was trying to say!

513
00:41:29,987 --> 00:41:30,821
Why?

514
00:41:35,576 --> 00:41:37,161
Because I thought I might die.

515
00:41:42,708 --> 00:41:45,044
I was scared I'd never get to tell you…

516
00:41:47,796 --> 00:41:50,174
that I wanted to be with you.

517
00:41:56,388 --> 00:41:57,765
Because I love you.

518
00:42:18,285 --> 00:42:19,161
You win.

519
00:42:21,247 --> 00:42:23,249
You win, Jae-mi. I lose.

520
00:42:23,916 --> 00:42:25,417
I surrender. Yeah.

521
00:42:26,794 --> 00:42:28,963
Then bow down to me. Go on!

522
00:42:30,047 --> 00:42:31,048
Yes, ma'am.

523
00:42:31,799 --> 00:42:34,218
What the heck? What are you doing?

524
00:42:34,301 --> 00:42:35,886
Hey, I'll bow down to you,

525
00:42:36,595 --> 00:42:38,138
if you promise me you'll stay.

526
00:42:38,222 --> 00:42:40,683
-Put me down now!
-Come on, promise me.

527
00:42:40,766 --> 00:42:41,934
Fine! I promise.

528
00:42:42,017 --> 00:42:45,813
By the way, I heard you.
You think the other shoes are prettier?

529
